parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or hesitate while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as whining
shuttering
or slipping sounds while driving
difficulty accelerating
or sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as slipping or jerking sensations while driving
difficulty accelerating
or sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as soft or spongy brake pedals
difficulty stopping
or complete brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator and cooling system can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit symptoms such as overheating
coolant leaks
or radiator fan failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including engine stalling, loss of power, or complete system failure.

engine stalling
or loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel bearings can cause wheel failure, leading to accidents or injuries.

vibrations

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly, leaving occupants unprotected.
symptoms: Airbag light stays on or flashes
airbag light comes on while driving
airbag light remains on even when passenger seat is occupied
airbag fails to deploy in a crash
seat belt light and airbag light never go off even after buckling in.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can lead to loss of control of the vehicle, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes all the way to the floor
car won't stop
brake pedal has a delayed response
brake failure leads to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can lead to the vehicle stalling or failing to start, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle engine stalls while driving
vehicle occasionally won't allow key to turn ignition
vehicle remains locked unpredictably.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the loss of power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The power steering warning light turns on
the power steering system fails to function
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle is hard to maneuver
and the steering wheel may seize or jerk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of vehicle stability and control can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle feels unstable
wanders
or drifts while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration and jerking can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates or jerks
